24:56.413 --> 24:58.248
Good to see you, buddy.

24:58.289 --> 24:59.541
Oh, what a trip.

24:59.582 --> 25:01.418
I got on the first flight out.

25:01.459 --> 25:03.628
Thanks, Frank. You been here before?

25:03.753 --> 25:07.048
The bar at the Woodcliff Lake,
New Jersey Hilton?

25:07.090 --> 25:08.133
No.

25:11.428 --> 25:13.722
- Oh, man.
- I, uh...

25:14.764 --> 25:18.268
Spoke to Sophie. She said...

25:19.602 --> 25:20.603
I did. I did.

25:20.645 --> 25:21.855
Josh.

25:21.938 --> 25:24.733
You wanna give us ice water

25:24.983 --> 25:27.736
for my handsome young friend here?

25:33.616 --> 25:35.243
Frank, I decided,

25:35.910 --> 25:38.288
uh, to make some changes in my life.

25:40.582 --> 25:43.418
Some of the changes
may come as a bit of a shock.

25:43.460 --> 25:46.379
Some may actually affect you, financially.

25:46.463 --> 25:49.924
I'm here as your friend, Danny.
Not as your manager.

25:51.426 --> 25:53.303
I want to cancel the rest of the tour.

25:54.262 --> 25:55.305
I'm sorry?

25:55.430 --> 25:57.140
I'm not sorry.

25:57.307 --> 25:59.017
I'm done, Frank.

25:59.768 --> 26:00.810
Done.

26:00.977 --> 26:02.979
So, help me, God,

26:03.021 --> 26:06.775
I will never be forced to sing
those songs again.

26:07.359 --> 26:08.693
Danny, you're spiraling.

26:08.818 --> 26:10.820
Are you on something?
What are you taking?

26:10.945 --> 26:13.782
I'm done with all of that shit too.

26:13.823 --> 26:15.075
No more, no more drinking,

26:15.158 --> 26:16.159
no more drugging.

26:16.201 --> 26:18.953
You're drinking right now, Danny.

26:20.163 --> 26:21.664
True.

26:21.706 --> 26:24.000
Let's forget about what
I said about drinking.

26:24.125 --> 26:26.503
I mean, I'm not running for Pope.

26:26.795 --> 26:28.171
And this is because of Sophie?

26:30.465 --> 26:31.966
Frank, please.

26:32.008 --> 26:34.511
Give me a little credit, will ya? Sophie?

26:38.848 --> 26:40.684
Okay. What would have happened

26:40.809 --> 26:43.353
if I got that letter
when I was supposed to?

26:44.062 --> 26:45.689
I would have called him.

26:46.022 --> 26:48.358
For sure as shit, I would have called him.

26:50.068 --> 26:53.029
Maybe my whole life
would have turned out different.

26:53.154 --> 26:54.572
Don't... Don't...

26:54.698 --> 26:57.575
You're too hard on yourself, kid.
You always have been. Now, come on.

26:57.659 --> 26:59.119
Frank.

26:59.703 --> 27:03.790
I haven't written a song in 30 years.
Thirty years.

27:04.749 --> 27:06.626
I'm a fucking joke.

27:08.712 --> 27:10.380
I'm an MC.

27:11.548 --> 27:14.884
A fuckin' court jester with a microphone.

27:16.720 --> 27:19.180
I was the real thing once.

27:19.556 --> 27:22.809
Right. I was the real thing.

27:22.892 --> 27:25.145
One album, my songs didn't sell,

27:25.854 --> 27:29.107
they handed me their songs to sing.
And I sung.

27:29.733 --> 27:31.484
- Mmm.
- I gave up.

27:31.776 --> 27:35.071
Danny, you're having a breakdown.

27:35.196 --> 27:39.242
I hate to tell you, buddy.
I've been breaking down for 40 years.

27:39.284 --> 27:41.578
I'm broken. Ain't nothin' left to break.

27:43.455 --> 27:46.916
I've been abusing my body
for the better part of four decades.

27:49.252 --> 27:51.963
If I'm going to find any
kind of redemption,

27:54.132 --> 27:56.801
I can't waste any more time.

27:59.095 --> 28:01.222
But why the fuck New Jersey?

28:02.766 --> 28:05.101
One shock at a time, Frank.

28:09.481 --> 28:10.774
Hey, Jamie.

28:10.899 --> 28:14.819
You talk to that kid Nicky Ernst
about that ride yet?

28:14.903 --> 28:16.112
Not yet, Mr. Collins.

28:16.446 --> 28:17.906
You got to do it.

28:17.947 --> 28:19.908
Uh, meet me at 7:00 for dinner.

28:19.949 --> 28:21.284
Still going to have to pass.

28:21.409 --> 28:22.744
Mary, you keep passing,

28:22.786 --> 28:25.622
I'll keep making passes
and we'll see who quits first.

28:26.081 --> 28:27.749
Have a nice day, Mr. Collins.

28:27.791 --> 28:31.836
Big day. Big day for me.
I'm meeting someone for the first time.

28:32.295 --> 28:33.797
How do I look?

28:35.131 --> 28:36.758
Honestly?

28:36.841 --> 28:38.677
If this relationship is
going to go the distance, Mary,

28:38.802 --> 28:40.562
I think we should
be honest with one another.

28:40.970 --> 28:43.223
Okay. Well,

28:43.306 --> 28:45.016
you look slightly ridiculous.

28:45.767 --> 28:48.895
Nah. I look sharp.

28:49.646 --> 28:51.940
- See you at 7:00.
- No, you won't.

28:51.981 --> 28:54.109
Hey, Jamie, don't forget about Nicky.

28:54.818 --> 28:56.444
He's a wonderful boy.

28:58.446 --> 28:59.864
Don't say anything to anyone.

29:00.490 --> 29:02.158
Nicky Ernst!

29:02.200 --> 29:03.243
It's ready for you, sir.

29:03.326 --> 29:05.620
Oh, man, I don't know what you did
to that girl inside,

29:05.662 --> 29:09.874
but, wow, all she does is talk about you.
Maybe you should ask her out.

29:09.958 --> 29:11.710
- Jamie?
- That's the one.

29:13.461 --> 29:15.880
Don't go after Mary. Mary's mine.

29:47.162 --> 29:48.538
I like your lawn.

29:50.957 --> 29:52.208
Thank you.

30:05.680 --> 30:06.681
Hello!

30:09.559 --> 30:10.560
Hello.

30:10.643 --> 30:12.979
Hope, you're not to
open the door to strangers.

30:13.063 --> 30:16.983
He's not a stranger, we saw him on TV.

30:17.067 --> 30:19.069
- Told you.
- Whoa!

30:19.152 --> 30:21.738
I told you.

30:21.821 --> 30:25.033
You didn't listen,
but I tried to tell you.

30:25.075 --> 30:28.411
I was unsure of, um, what was appropriate.

30:28.495 --> 30:29.662
He's at work.

30:29.913 --> 30:32.499
I brought bagels.

30:34.918 --> 30:37.754
One, two, three...

30:37.879 --> 30:43.343
<i>The itsy-bitsy spider
came up the water spout</i>

30:43.426 --> 30:44.594
Yeah.

30:44.678 --> 30:50.725
<i>Down came the rain
and it washed the spider out</i>

30:51.434 --> 30:56.940
<i>Out came the sun and dried up all the rain</i>

30:57.649 --> 31:02.404
<i>And the itsy-bitsy spider</i>

31:02.445 --> 31:06.783
<i>Climbed up the spout again</i>

31:06.950 --> 31:10.620
That's beautiful.
You have a natural singing voice.

31:12.122 --> 31:13.581
Oh, my God.

31:13.623 --> 31:15.083
Just comes out naturally.

31:15.125 --> 31:16.960
How did you find us?

31:17.752 --> 31:19.045
Oh, well, you know,

31:19.129 --> 31:21.798
I had tracked him down years ago, you know,

31:21.881 --> 31:25.301
just never got the nerve up to,
uh, come see him.

31:27.137 --> 31:28.179
I want a bagel.

31:28.555 --> 31:29.848
Can I have a bagel, Mom?

31:29.973 --> 31:32.726
Yeah. Okay. Let me just...

31:32.809 --> 31:35.645
Wow. On so many levels. Wow.

31:35.729 --> 31:37.772
How far along are you?

31:37.897 --> 31:39.733
With... Oh, um...

31:40.150 --> 31:41.651
- Six months, more or less.
- Oh.

31:42.444 --> 31:44.738
Uh, boy or girl? You know?

31:45.280 --> 31:46.406
It's a boy.

31:46.573 --> 31:49.617
Oh. Boy. Wow.

31:50.076 --> 31:51.453
On so many levels.

31:55.123 --> 31:57.167
I have to call him.
I mean, I have to call him.

31:57.292 --> 31:58.960
Oh, yeah, sure.

31:59.336 --> 32:01.004
Sure. Sure. Sure.

32:01.087 --> 32:03.423
I just finished the first grade.

32:03.673 --> 32:07.010
And my teacher is named Mrs. Williams.

32:07.594 --> 32:11.056
Her aunt died last week,
so we had a substitute.

32:11.348 --> 32:14.184
He had a mustache.

32:14.267 --> 32:15.518
She had a mustache?

32:15.602 --> 32:17.896
- He.
- Oh, it was a he. Oh, okay.

32:18.021 --> 32:19.856
Why are you on TV?

32:19.939 --> 32:21.900
Because I'm a singer.

32:21.983 --> 32:24.569
Are you a good singer?

32:24.652 --> 32:27.947
Well, I don't know, you know, not really.

32:28.031 --> 32:29.282
- I didn't think so.
- Hope.

32:29.366 --> 32:30.367
You didn't think so?

32:31.326 --> 32:35.205
And why didn't you think so?

32:35.288 --> 32:40.543
Because when you were on the TV,
my daddy said, "Shut it off, Samantha!"

32:40.627 --> 32:42.879
And Mommy turned it off really fast.

32:42.962 --> 32:46.966
And Mommy said, "Tom..."
And Daddy said, "N-O."

32:47.050 --> 32:49.427
And that was that.

32:49.761 --> 32:50.762
Wow.

32:50.845 --> 32:53.223
But I thought you were great. Really.

32:53.306 --> 32:54.891
You thought I was good?

32:54.974 --> 32:58.061
Danny Collins showed up at our house.

32:58.144 --> 32:59.145
Mmm-hmm.

32:59.646 --> 33:01.690
He's having bagels in
the kitchen with Hope.

33:01.773 --> 33:03.213
Why don't we take a break from that?

33:03.274 --> 33:04.859
Okay. Let's just color.

33:05.402 --> 33:07.654
Look at this. Startin' to get it.

33:07.737 --> 33:08.988
What was I supposed to do?

33:09.072 --> 33:10.949
Why don't you do it really slow?

33:11.032 --> 33:13.660
I do, yes, I do. Okay.

33:14.411 --> 33:16.538
- Bye, honey.
- Slowly makes it more...

33:16.579 --> 33:17.914
Didn't I already color that?

33:17.997 --> 33:20.375
You did. You told me that.

33:20.458 --> 33:21.501
Well, he's coming home.

33:21.918 --> 33:22.961
Yay!

33:23.044 --> 33:24.462
Daddy's coming home.

33:24.629 --> 33:27.716
That should be, uh, interesting.

33:27.924 --> 33:30.051
This is going to be interesting.

33:30.844 --> 33:34.055
- Mommy, look! It's <i>Yo Gabba Gabba!
</i>-I see it.

33:34.139 --> 33:37.934
The orange alien guy
has one eye just in the middle.

33:38.309 --> 33:40.478
Look, it's on TV!

33:40.770 --> 33:42.897
- Whoo-hoo!
- Hey, Hope. Settle. Calm.

33:44.899 --> 33:46.609
Thank you. Okay.

33:46.901 --> 33:51.364
Uh, she seems a little, uh, energetic.

33:52.240 --> 33:54.409
Or severely hyperactive.

33:54.451 --> 33:56.786
You know ADHD, it's the thing.

33:57.662 --> 34:00.540
Learning issues, behavioral stuff, all of it.

34:00.665 --> 34:04.044
We do the best we can, but it's a battle.

34:05.545 --> 34:07.339
Why are you here?

34:08.590 --> 34:10.091
Well, you know,

34:11.009 --> 34:12.594
I'm just, uh...

34:14.471 --> 34:16.097
Making some changes in my life.

34:17.599 --> 34:19.119
It's a little late for that, isn't it?

34:21.186 --> 34:24.647
Maybe. I don't know. I hope not.

34:28.275 --> 34:30.445
Tom's the best man I've ever met.

34:31.571 --> 34:33.072
He's solid,

34:33.739 --> 34:35.492
kind, funny.

34:35.533 --> 34:39.245
We've had one fight in 12 years,
we've had one serious fight.

34:41.121 --> 34:44.501
A couple years ago I got backstage passes
for one of your shows.

34:44.583 --> 34:45.668
I thought it was...

34:45.710 --> 34:50.340
You know, he should at least
meet you, right? After all this time?

34:51.549 --> 34:52.842
He disagreed.

34:54.260 --> 34:57.222
He disagreed strongly.

34:58.890 --> 35:00.600
So, this is not going to be pretty?

35:00.684 --> 35:02.811
I wouldn't think so, no.

35:02.852 --> 35:03.895
Okay.

35:06.564 --> 35:09.317
So, you think maybe, uh, you know,

35:09.401 --> 35:12.362
you could help grease the wheels a little?

35:12.404 --> 35:14.197
Mr. Collins.

35:15.740 --> 35:18.326
My parents are dead. His mom is, too.

35:18.451 --> 35:22.664
I mean, I would love for our children
to know their one remaining grandparent.

35:22.706 --> 35:26.501
I would love for my husband
to know his father.

35:26.710 --> 35:28.920
In a few minutes, my husband
is going to walk through that door

35:29.004 --> 35:33.842
and when he does, I feel pretty confident
this will be the last time I ever see you.

35:34.217 --> 35:38.930
And despite your celebrity,
and despite what I want for my own family,

35:39.014 --> 35:41.266
I will not try to stop that.

35:41.349 --> 35:43.059
You did this.

35:43.184 --> 35:45.854
You did this to yourself.

35:45.895 --> 35:48.023
Shame on you.

35:50.066 --> 35:51.359
That was good.

35:53.361 --> 35:54.904
Thanks. I've been practicing

35:54.988 --> 35:56.614
- since you gave me the bagels.

35:56.698 --> 35:59.576
It has a certain feel to it.

35:59.659 --> 36:01.077
Oh, he married well.

36:01.453 --> 36:04.748
- He did. I'm great.
- Yeah.

36:04.831 --> 36:06.499
See what you missed out on?

36:07.459 --> 36:09.002
Perfect daughter-in-law.

36:13.423 --> 36:14.632
Well...

36:19.429 --> 36:21.431
Daddy! Daddy!

36:21.765 --> 36:26.186
Look who it is, it's the man from TV!
It's the man from TV that we saw singing!

36:26.269 --> 36:28.271
- And Mommy said...
- Easy...

36:28.355 --> 36:30.940
And he brought bagels. He brought bagels.

36:31.024 --> 36:33.276
Mommy called you. And you're home early.

36:33.318 --> 36:35.445
Hope, your favorite flower is a...

36:35.528 --> 36:36.529
Rose.

36:36.613 --> 36:39.324
To smell it, you breathe through your...

36:40.533 --> 36:42.535
Keep it in, long as you can go.

36:43.119 --> 36:46.122
Then let it out in one big...

36:47.123 --> 36:49.167
...Blow.

36:51.753 --> 36:53.797
- Hi, honey.
- Hey, baby.

36:57.175 --> 36:58.968
Speak to you outside for a second?

36:59.803 --> 37:01.763
Of course. Sure.

37:03.640 --> 37:04.724
Okay.

37:05.392 --> 37:06.393
Um...

37:06.810 --> 37:08.645
If I have,

37:08.728 --> 37:11.439
I am truly very sorry,

37:11.481 --> 37:13.692
that I missed out on you.

37:15.902 --> 37:17.987
Thank you for the bagels.

37:18.363 --> 37:19.364
Okay.

37:19.489 --> 37:21.324
Hope, say goodbye to Mr. Collins.

37:21.408 --> 37:23.159
Goodbye, Mr. Collins.

37:23.201 --> 37:25.328
Mr. Collins, say goodbye to Hope.

37:28.373 --> 37:30.917
Goodbye to Hope.

37:36.006 --> 37:37.549
Come here.

37:45.348 --> 37:47.267
You're so tall.

37:48.518 --> 37:50.562
I'm sorry, what exactly do you want?

37:53.106 --> 37:55.442
- Well, you know...
- Are you sick?

37:55.525 --> 37:57.777
Is that what you're doing here?
Are you dying?

37:57.861 --> 37:59.529
No, I'm not sick.

38:01.865 --> 38:03.366
You have every right to be angry.

38:03.450 --> 38:06.453
No. No. I'm not angry. Really, I'm not.

38:06.536 --> 38:10.248
I'm a little confused,
and strangely, not interested.

38:10.707 --> 38:12.667
So, if you have anything to ask me,
just go ahead.

38:12.709 --> 38:15.712
'Cause this is the last time
we'll see each other.

38:17.964 --> 38:19.257
So, what do you do for a living?

38:19.382 --> 38:23.094
I work construction. Local, residential.

38:23.219 --> 38:25.722
It's not my dream job, but it's steady,

38:25.805 --> 38:28.558
and, you know,
Princeton wasn't exactly in the cards.

38:28.600 --> 38:29.601
What else?

38:29.726 --> 38:31.519
Your mom?

38:31.561 --> 38:32.896
She, uh...

38:32.979 --> 38:34.481
She died of cancer 10 years ago.

38:35.940 --> 38:38.651
Never married, never spoke about you

38:38.735 --> 38:41.404
except to say that it was a wild thing
she did when she was 23

38:41.446 --> 38:43.446
and got drunk backstage
after one of your concerts.

38:43.490 --> 38:45.617
I use her last name. Anything else?

38:45.742 --> 38:47.243
You're clearly angry.

38:47.285 --> 38:48.453
Look, I don't care enough to be angry.

38:48.578 --> 38:51.081
I am wondering what I'm going
to tell my little girl about who you are.

38:51.122 --> 38:53.249
And I'm thinking,
I have to be back at work in 20 minutes.

38:53.333 --> 38:55.085
Are we done here?

38:55.168 --> 38:56.169
I sent checks.

38:56.252 --> 38:57.671
- I ripped them up, okay?
- Okay.

38:57.754 --> 39:00.256
Okay. Nice to meet you. Have a good life.

39:01.591 --> 39:03.093
Are you happy?

39:03.301 --> 39:04.928
Am I happy?

39:05.637 --> 39:06.846
I don't know.

39:08.264 --> 39:10.433
You have a happy life?

39:15.605 --> 39:17.273
I hate my boss.

39:18.817 --> 39:21.277
Fucking Mets break my heart every year.

39:22.654 --> 39:26.032
But I have the most amazing wife
in the history of wives,

39:26.116 --> 39:28.118
and an amazing little girl.

39:28.159 --> 39:30.870
One that I wish I could do more for.
That I really wish I could do.

39:30.954 --> 39:33.081
But you know what,
if it makes you sleep better at night,

39:33.123 --> 39:34.666
yeah, I'm happy.

39:35.959 --> 39:38.628
And fuck you, you selfish prick, I am angry.

40:26.134 --> 40:27.886
Mr. Collins.

40:28.178 --> 40:30.430
- How we doing tonight?
- Oh.

40:31.681 --> 40:34.392
Peachy. Thank you for asking.

40:35.018 --> 40:38.063
Oh, good. I'm really glad to hear that.

40:38.146 --> 40:39.814
Mr. Collins,

40:39.856 --> 40:41.896
I was wondering if you could
help me with something.

40:42.359 --> 40:44.569
- Shoot.
- Okay.

40:44.694 --> 40:48.156
When a famous musician starts getting
fall-down drunk in a hotel bar

40:48.198 --> 40:50.158
and you're the manager of that hotel,

40:50.200 --> 40:53.536
is there a protocol
on how to handle the situation?

40:54.204 --> 40:55.330
Because actually,

40:55.372 --> 40:58.541
we have had a shortage of
famous fall-down drunk musicians lately,

40:58.667 --> 41:00.710
I'm a bit out of my depth.

41:03.588 --> 41:04.881
I see.

41:05.840 --> 41:09.386
Well, you know, I had a bad day.

41:09.511 --> 41:11.888
Oh. Okay.

41:12.013 --> 41:13.598
This is just water.

41:13.723 --> 41:15.225
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

41:15.350 --> 41:17.394
Yeah, that's just because
you drank all the booze

41:17.435 --> 41:18.895
and the ice is melted.

41:19.521 --> 41:22.107
Don't be mean to me.
I really had a bad day.

41:22.232 --> 41:23.233
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

41:24.901 --> 41:27.821
- Well, I had a bad day too.
- Yeah?

41:29.698 --> 41:31.116
Can I buy you a drink?

41:31.783 --> 41:33.743
Bay Breeze?

41:34.035 --> 41:36.788
Wine spritzer?
Maybe even one of those frozen...

41:36.913 --> 41:42.293
Josh, give me tequila, rocks,
something <i>aÃ±ejo,</i> and a splash of soda.

41:42.377 --> 41:44.546
Right away, boss.

41:44.879 --> 41:47.549
You're not the only rock
star in this hotel.

41:47.590 --> 41:48.925
Apparently not.

41:50.969 --> 41:53.471
- So, you had a bad day?
- Mmm.

41:53.596 --> 41:55.265
Why'd you have a bad day?

41:57.308 --> 42:00.812
Okay, I work with a bunch of well-meaning...
Thank you.

42:00.937 --> 42:02.731
But remarkably dim twenty-somethings

42:02.772 --> 42:04.983
who are just passing time
until they go back to college.

42:05.108 --> 42:07.068
And one of them
screwed up the computer system

42:07.110 --> 42:11.614
and it took me half the day
to reprogram every reservation manually.

42:14.159 --> 42:16.286
Mmm. Ah.

42:18.288 --> 42:19.456
What about you?

42:21.916 --> 42:25.795
I tracked down my grown son,

42:25.920 --> 42:27.797
who I've never met before.

42:29.257 --> 42:34.179
I met him, his wife, my granddaughter.

42:35.472 --> 42:39.142
And then he told me, quite emphatically,

42:40.310 --> 42:43.772
to fuck off and to die.

42:48.026 --> 42:50.320
Well, it was every reservation,

42:50.445 --> 42:54.991
each one had to be reprogrammed manually.
I hope I made that clear.

42:57.035 --> 42:58.828
Can I ask you a question?

43:00.163 --> 43:04.376
Not if it's about why
I never met my son until today.

43:04.542 --> 43:07.295
