01:21:29.389 --> 01:21:30.807
- Grandpa?
- Honey.

01:21:32.142 --> 01:21:34.728
<i>Hey, baby doll</i>

01:21:34.811 --> 01:21:37.105
<i>What's goin' on?</i>

01:21:37.188 --> 01:21:38.481
Come here. Come on.

01:21:38.565 --> 01:21:40.233
- Dad! What you doing?
- Go to Mommy. It's okay.

01:21:40.358 --> 01:21:41.985
What are you doing? What are you doing?

01:21:42.068 --> 01:21:44.195
Wasn't doing anything. I didn't know, uh...

01:21:44.279 --> 01:21:46.531
I didn't know... Hi, Samantha. Hi.

01:21:47.198 --> 01:21:52.537
This is my friend Sophie there.
And her friend, Busywork.

01:21:53.038 --> 01:21:54.372
So what's goin' on?

01:21:55.415 --> 01:21:57.417
What's the look?

01:21:58.126 --> 01:21:59.127
Oh.

01:21:59.252 --> 01:22:00.962
You just keep judging me, Tom.

01:22:01.838 --> 01:22:02.839
You just judge me. Go ahead.

01:22:02.922 --> 01:22:05.842
You judge me all you want.
It's fine, that's what you're good at.

01:22:06.676 --> 01:22:08.970
And when you're done,

01:22:09.054 --> 01:22:11.181
you know, being so fucking perfect

01:22:11.890 --> 01:22:13.975
and honorable,

01:22:14.059 --> 01:22:16.853
you should talk to your wife
about what you did in Delaware.

01:22:20.607 --> 01:22:24.652
What's that? What's he mean? Tom?

01:22:26.654 --> 01:22:28.531
I'll tell you when we get home.

01:22:35.663 --> 01:22:37.415
Stay the fuck away from my family.

01:22:37.499 --> 01:22:39.834
Tom. Let's go.

01:22:46.091 --> 01:22:47.592
Bye, Hope.

01:22:56.976 --> 01:22:58.770
Oh, man.

01:23:31.386 --> 01:23:34.347
Come on, let's get the fuck out of here.

01:24:11.176 --> 01:24:12.802
Who are you?

01:24:14.721 --> 01:24:17.307
Oh, I'm sorry, I work for the hotel.

01:24:17.349 --> 01:24:18.350
Oh, good. That's good.

01:24:19.309 --> 01:24:21.311
We need more towels. Can you do that?

01:24:21.394 --> 01:24:22.979
Mary!

01:24:23.021 --> 01:24:24.314
- And some beer.
- Oh, Mary.

01:24:24.397 --> 01:24:27.233
I'll get you some towels and some beer.

01:24:33.490 --> 01:24:36.534
Mary, wait, wait, wait.

01:24:36.659 --> 01:24:38.244
Mary, please.

01:24:41.206 --> 01:24:43.583
- It's not...
- What happened last night?

01:24:44.542 --> 01:24:46.169
Well, you know...

01:24:46.211 --> 01:24:50.340
I just... It wasn't right, you know?
It wasn't the right time.

01:24:50.382 --> 01:24:52.509
What are you talking about?

01:24:52.592 --> 01:24:55.512
You've worked so hard
and your whole family was there.

01:24:55.595 --> 01:24:56.596
- I know.
- Come on!

01:24:56.680 --> 01:24:58.056
I just couldn't...

01:24:59.182 --> 01:25:00.266
I lost my nerve.

01:25:00.350 --> 01:25:02.519
Oh, well, you lost your dinner, too.

01:25:03.186 --> 01:25:04.437
Okay...

01:25:04.521 --> 01:25:06.690
You should have played the song, Danny.

01:25:06.773 --> 01:25:09.234
You should have at least played
the one fucking song.

01:25:20.120 --> 01:25:21.705
Take care, Jamie.

01:25:22.789 --> 01:25:24.874
You, too, Mr. Collins.

01:25:24.916 --> 01:25:28.378
You be good to Nicky. He's a good boy.
You got a wonderful face.

01:25:29.713 --> 01:25:32.924
- Yours isn't so bad either, Mr. Collins.
- Oh.

01:25:33.049 --> 01:25:35.719
Look at that. Now we're getting patter.

01:25:40.557 --> 01:25:41.766
Okay.

01:25:45.061 --> 01:25:47.939
You know, for the record, uh,

01:25:49.065 --> 01:25:53.278
Mary Ann from <i>Gilligan's Island,</i>

01:25:54.070 --> 01:25:56.740
her real name was Dawn Wells.

01:25:56.823 --> 01:26:00.410
And she was Miss Nevada
before she got famous

01:26:00.493 --> 01:26:03.496
and she couldn't hold
a fucking candle to you.

01:26:13.131 --> 01:26:14.132
Bye.

01:26:20.889 --> 01:26:23.641
Nicky. Oh, Nicky.

01:26:24.100 --> 01:26:25.602
What a pleasure it's been.

01:26:25.685 --> 01:26:27.812
Pleasure's definitely been all mine, Danny.

01:26:27.896 --> 01:26:31.441
I'm gonna miss you. Gonna miss you.

01:26:32.567 --> 01:26:34.194
Look at this.

01:26:34.402 --> 01:26:35.695
Ran out of hundreds.

01:26:35.779 --> 01:26:37.989
Don't even worry about it. Come on.

01:26:38.073 --> 01:26:40.283
I'll tell you what.

01:26:41.451 --> 01:26:44.120
I'm in a giving vein today.

01:26:50.168 --> 01:26:51.961
Come on, get outta here.
What are you talking about?

01:26:52.045 --> 01:26:56.257
The second you stop appreciating
this piece of machinery,

01:26:56.341 --> 01:26:58.176
then you give it to somebody else.

01:26:58.259 --> 01:26:59.511
Deal?

01:27:00.428 --> 01:27:01.429
Deal.

01:27:03.306 --> 01:27:04.683
Go ahead, man.

01:27:06.101 --> 01:27:07.477
God bless you, Danny Collins.

01:27:07.560 --> 01:27:08.895
Back at ya.

01:27:09.145 --> 01:27:10.480
Whoo!

01:27:10.522 --> 01:27:12.607
How much does insurance even cost...

01:27:12.691 --> 01:27:15.026
Fuck it, I don't care. I don't care.

01:27:15.694 --> 01:27:16.778
- Watch your head.
- Okay.

01:27:25.995 --> 01:27:27.288
Okay, Danny.

01:27:28.498 --> 01:27:30.959
I don't want the last thing
I ever said to you to be mean,

01:27:31.042 --> 01:27:33.294
but I don't want to say anything nice.

01:27:33.378 --> 01:27:35.255
So, Mr. Collins,

01:27:35.338 --> 01:27:38.758
on behalf of the Woodcliff Lake Hilton,
we'd like to thank you for your stay.

01:27:39.676 --> 01:27:44.264
And we hope that you will make Hilton
a home wherever your travels take you.

01:27:46.516 --> 01:27:48.852
I'm grabbing a cab.

01:27:49.894 --> 01:27:51.062
I see that.

01:27:51.146 --> 01:27:54.899
I gave Nicky my Mercedes.

01:27:55.942 --> 01:27:59.654
You gave your Mercedes to Nicky?
You are fucking crazy.

01:27:59.738 --> 01:28:02.907
It's been said, yes. I
can afford it, though.

01:28:02.991 --> 01:28:05.785
Frank called me this morning
and we're going back on tour.

01:28:06.161 --> 01:28:09.831
I need the money. I got a family now.

01:28:10.206 --> 01:28:11.708
So...

01:28:11.791 --> 01:28:14.627
They hate my guts, but, uh...

01:28:14.711 --> 01:28:16.504
I'm told that's what families do.

01:28:16.963 --> 01:28:19.424
Yeah, that's right. I've taught you well.

01:28:19.841 --> 01:28:23.845
Yeah. I'm going to play my new songs.

01:28:24.304 --> 01:28:27.474
- Some of them. We'll see what happens.
- Ah.

01:28:28.266 --> 01:28:29.559
I know what will happen.

01:28:29.934 --> 01:28:33.688
- Yeah, they'll throw tomatoes at me.
- Yeah, and onions.

01:28:36.983 --> 01:28:39.819
You know, I'm going to be here
in a couple of months.

01:28:39.903 --> 01:28:42.322
You know, in the area.
We're playing the Garden.

01:28:42.489 --> 01:28:43.490
Oh.

01:28:43.740 --> 01:28:45.533
Yeah, maybe you'll come by, see the show.

01:28:45.575 --> 01:28:49.204
We'll have, uh, dinner afterwards.

01:28:49.287 --> 01:28:51.623
You know what I like about you?
You never give up.

01:28:53.291 --> 01:28:55.502
Some dinners are worth fighting for.

01:29:00.632 --> 01:29:03.885
I left something in the room for ya.

01:29:03.968 --> 01:29:07.263
