01:29:07.347 --> 01:29:10.475
Well, you know, rock stars.

01:29:13.937 --> 01:29:15.397
So, uh...

01:29:17.524 --> 01:29:19.776
Another life, huh?

01:29:21.403 --> 01:29:23.446
You never know.

01:30:25.091 --> 01:30:27.302
- Oh. Hi.
- Hey.

01:30:27.427 --> 01:30:31.097
Hi, sorry, I don't think we met.
I'm Mary, the hotel manager.

01:30:31.181 --> 01:30:33.141
- You must be Busywork?
- Yeah.

01:30:33.183 --> 01:30:35.435
Uh, I'm Judd.

01:30:35.560 --> 01:30:38.688
- Judd, yeah, right. Okay, very good.
- Yeah, yeah.

01:30:38.772 --> 01:30:41.191
- Anyway, checkout's noon.
- Sweet.

01:31:09.886 --> 01:31:13.056
Christ, what, did he send you out here
to check up on me?

01:31:13.139 --> 01:31:15.558
Well, the hotel didn't know what to do
with the damn piano.

01:31:15.642 --> 01:31:17.477
So I thought you might want it.

01:31:17.560 --> 01:31:19.729
- I don't want his piano.
- Yeah?

01:31:19.854 --> 01:31:22.357
Well, it took six hours
to move it out of the Hilton

01:31:22.399 --> 01:31:25.068
and I don't know anyone else in New Jersey.
So tough shit.

01:31:26.486 --> 01:31:32.200
Look, it's a $30,000 instrument, Tom.
Sell it, for all I care.

01:31:36.705 --> 01:31:38.248
How's your health?

01:31:39.833 --> 01:31:41.501
I find out in a few days.

01:31:41.710 --> 01:31:42.711
Ah.

01:31:43.670 --> 01:31:45.255
Your age.

01:31:48.258 --> 01:31:51.261
You know, when I was in my 30s,
I started drinking, heavily.

01:31:52.095 --> 01:31:55.098
Ah. Long line of drunks in my family.

01:31:55.557 --> 01:31:57.767
All with the usual bullshit excuses.

01:31:57.892 --> 01:32:00.270
Careful, gentlemen!

01:32:00.395 --> 01:32:02.939
That is a Steinway!

01:32:03.064 --> 01:32:04.607
Yes, sir!

01:32:04.941 --> 01:32:10.238
Anyway, we were on tour in the Bay Area.
I fell asleep at the wheel.

01:32:10.780 --> 01:32:12.907
Almost killed myself and others.

01:32:12.949 --> 01:32:14.951
Danny bailed me out.

01:32:15.035 --> 01:32:19.122
5:00 in the morning, he shows up
at the San Jose police station,

01:32:19.247 --> 01:32:20.540
wacked out of his skull.

01:32:21.541 --> 01:32:27.464
He drives me six hours
to this Hollywood rehab joint

01:32:27.589 --> 01:32:30.216
drunker than I'd been the night before,
the dumb shit.

01:32:31.051 --> 01:32:34.804
He visited me every
Saturday till I got dry,

01:32:34.888 --> 01:32:37.932
and then once a week for 37 years,

01:32:37.974 --> 01:32:44.356
I get four cases of bottled water,
sent to me wherever I am in the world.

01:32:45.106 --> 01:32:47.108
Always with the same note.

01:32:47.150 --> 01:32:51.071
"Drink as many as you want. On me. Danny."

01:32:55.992 --> 01:32:58.328
Best friend I ever had, your father.

01:33:01.831 --> 01:33:06.086
Yeah, the man saved my life
and got me stone-cold sober.

01:33:06.169 --> 01:33:10.173
And was three sheets to the wind
the whole time he was doing it.

01:33:10.298 --> 01:33:12.842
I'm sorry, but I'm not seeing your point.

01:33:12.926 --> 01:33:15.345
The point, my boy,

01:33:16.179 --> 01:33:18.181
is that he's got a good heart.

01:33:18.807 --> 01:33:21.184
He just keeps it up his ass half the time.

01:33:22.769 --> 01:33:26.106
What you do with that is up to you.

01:33:26.815 --> 01:33:30.026
My waters will keep coming, no matter what.

01:33:30.527 --> 01:33:33.363
All right, boys, let's move that puppy!

01:33:33.446 --> 01:33:35.490
So I can get the fuck out of New Jersey.

01:33:47.335 --> 01:33:50.463
So I'll see you guys in Pittsburgh?

01:33:50.547 --> 01:33:55.885
Yeah. Frank is setting up the other events.
Okay, talk soon.

01:34:02.726 --> 01:34:05.812
Okay. Now let's take a look
at the computer system.

01:34:05.895 --> 01:34:07.731
I still don't know...

01:34:36.676 --> 01:34:38.678
Have fun at the doctor.

01:34:56.446 --> 01:34:58.948
Your favorite flower is...

01:35:00.617 --> 01:35:02.077
Rose.

01:35:02.410 --> 01:35:05.455
To smell it you breathe through your...

01:35:06.623 --> 01:35:11.378
Hold it in as long as you can go,
and let it out in one big...

01:36:39.507 --> 01:36:42.385
Hi. Tom Donnelly for Dr. Silverman.

01:36:42.469 --> 01:36:45.096
Sure. Just have a seat, Mr. Donnelly.

01:37:11.164 --> 01:37:13.541
So, uh, she's pissed?

01:37:13.583 --> 01:37:16.086
Nah, she's thrilled. Thanks for asking.

01:37:18.254 --> 01:37:21.591
Oh, that was such a horrible night for me.
It's no excuse.

01:37:21.716 --> 01:37:24.928
Well, I can assure you
it was a worse night for me.

01:37:30.433 --> 01:37:32.811
So she's not going to come at all?

01:37:38.525 --> 01:37:40.068
She can barely move.

01:37:41.444 --> 01:37:44.656
Doctor's got her on full bed rest now.

01:37:46.074 --> 01:37:48.785
Plus whatever this news is,
I'd rather she heard it from me.

01:37:48.868 --> 01:37:50.120
Not some doctor.

01:37:51.329 --> 01:37:52.706
Mr. Donnelly?

01:38:19.607 --> 01:38:21.651
Listen, if this news is bad...

01:38:22.444 --> 01:38:23.445
Tom...

01:38:23.486 --> 01:38:25.238
No, listen to me. Uh...

01:38:26.489 --> 01:38:28.241
If it's bad,

01:38:29.117 --> 01:38:31.161
Samantha, Hope and the baby...

01:38:31.244 --> 01:38:32.787
They'll be taken care of, Tom.

01:38:33.663 --> 01:38:36.124
- Don't even think about it.
- Okay.

01:38:36.166 --> 01:38:39.294
Okay. Good. Thank you.

01:38:45.300 --> 01:38:47.302
