Okay, Tom, so here's where we are.

01:41:51.528 --> 01:41:53.697
<i>What happened was I did an interview</i>

01:41:53.780 --> 01:41:58.451
with a magazine called <i>Zig Zag</i> in 1971.

01:41:58.535 --> 01:42:01.371
Just after I've had my first album out.

01:42:01.454 --> 01:42:04.833
And in it, I was asked by the fellow
who was interviewing me

01:42:04.874 --> 01:42:06.376
whether I thought...

01:42:06.459 --> 01:42:07.877
If I, um...

01:42:09.212 --> 01:42:14.217
If I became, you know, rich
beyond the dreams of avarice, you know,

01:42:14.342 --> 01:42:18.054
whether it would affect my song writing,
you know, detrimentally.

01:42:18.179 --> 01:42:20.390
And I thought... I said I thought it would.

01:42:20.473 --> 01:42:22.684
Anyway, John, for some reason,

01:42:22.726 --> 01:42:25.645
took an exception to this
and wrote a letter in.

01:42:41.077 --> 01:42:43.413
<i>It was a very friendly letter.</i>

01:42:45.081 --> 01:42:49.252
<i>And he finished it with,
"Well, what do you think of that?"</i>

01:42:49.502 --> 01:42:52.213
<i>He had his own home
telephone number in Ascot.</i>

01:42:52.255 --> 01:42:56.092
<i>So, if I had got the letter, you know,
when he sent it, I would have rung him.</i>

01:42:56.176 --> 01:42:57.260
<i>Right, yeah.</i>

